"title": "8756: folly, examples of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8756",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Human folly is seen in rebellion against God, ignoring his way and will, a failure to understand him: and moral or spiritual irresponsibility.</p>\n<h2>Examples of human folly</h2>\n<h3>The folly of God's people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer4:22\">JER 4:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:6\">DEU 32:6</a> <em>rejecting God</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer10:8\">JER 10:8</a> <em>worshipping idols</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos7:11\">HOS 7:11</a> <em>seeking foreign help rather than trusting God</em></p>\n<h3>The folly of Israel's leaders</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer10:21\">JER 10:21</a></strong> <em>The shepherds are those entrusted with the task of guiding and caring for God's people</em>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek13:3\">EZK 13:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:16-Matt23:17\">MAT 23:16–23:17</a></p>\n<h3>Particular demonstrations of human folly</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num12:1-Num12:11\">NUM 12:1–12:11</a> <em>Aaron and Miriam</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam13:13\">1SA 13:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam26:21\">1SA 26:21</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:25\">1SA 25:25</a> <em>Nabal. In Hebrew this name means “fool”.</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam24:10\">2SA 24:10</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr21:8\">1CH 21:8</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr16:7-2Chr16:9\">2CH 16:7–16:9</a> <em>Asa, king of Judah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa19:11-Isa19:13\">ISA 19:11–19:13</a> <em>Pharaoh's advisors</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:26\">MAT 7:26</a> <em>the foolish builder</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:1-Matt25:3\">MAT 25:1–25:3</a> <em>the foolish virgins</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:16-Luke12:21\">LUK 12:16–12:21</a> <em>the rich fool</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:13\">GAL 3:13</a> <em>the Galatian Christians</em></p>\n<h2>Paul's ``foolishness''</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:16-2Cor11:21\">2CO 11:16–11:21</a></strong> <em>Paul engages in what he admits is the foolish boasting of his accomplishments in order to challenge the claims of false “apostles”.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:1\">2CO 11:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:6\">2CO 12:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:11\">2CO 12:11</a></p>\n<h2>God's wisdom regarded as ``foolishness''</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:18\">1CO 1:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos9:7\">HOS 9:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech11:15\">ZEC 11:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:20-1Cor1:25\">1CO 1:20–1:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:27\">1CO 1:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:10\">1CO 4:10</a></p>\n<h2>Human wisdom is foolishness to God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:19\">1CO 3:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job12:17\">JOB 12:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa29:14\">ISA 29:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:25\">ISA 44:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa55:8\">ISA 55:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer50:36\">JER 50:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:22\">ROM 1:22</a></p>",
